{meta: title Across The Border}
{meta: artist Linda Ronstadt and Emmylou Harris}
{meta: composer Bruce Springsteen}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]Tonight my bag is packed
[C]Tomorrow I'll walk these [G]tracks
[D7]That will lead me across the [G]border
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
Tomorrow my love and I
[C]Will sleep 'neath auburn [G]skies
[D7]Somewhere across the [G]border
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[C]We'll leave behind my dear
[D7]The pain and sadness we found here
[G]And we'll drink from the Brazos muddy [C]waters
[G]Where the sky grows gray and wide
[C]We'll meet on the other [G]side
[D7]There across the [G]border
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[C]For me you'll build a house
[G]High up on a grassy hill
[D7]Somewhere across the [G]border
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
Where pain and memory
[C]Pain and memory have been [G]stilled
[D7]There across the [G]border
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
[C]And sweet blossoms fill the air
[D7]Pastures of gold and green
[G]Roll down into cool clear [C]waters
[G]And in your arms 'neath the open skies
[C]I'll kiss the sorrow from your [G]eyes
[D7]There across the [G]border
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 7}
[C]Tonight we'll sing the songs
[D7]I'll dream of you my Corazon
[G]And tomorrow my heart will be [C]strong
[G]And may the saints blessing and grace
[C]Carry me safely into your [G]arms
[D7]There across the [G]border
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 8}
[C]For what are we
[D7]Without hope in our hearts
[G]That someday we'll drink from God's blessed [C]waters
[G]And eat the fruit from the vine
[C]I know love and fortune will be [G]mine
[D7]Somewhere across the [G]border
{end_of_verse}
